@startuml ticket-message-reply-note-attachments
title Ticket Message, Reply, Note, Attachments, and SLA Side Effects
hide footbox
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
}

actor "Agent" as Agent
participant "Ticket UI" as UI
participant "Routes +\nValidation" as Routes
participant "Auth + Workspace\nGuards" as Guards
participant "Message\nController" as Controller
participant "Ticket Message\nService" as MessageService
participant "Ticket + Conversation\nModels" as TicketModels
participant "Message\nModel" as MessageModel
participant "File + Link\nServices/Models" as FileServices
participant "SLA Runtime\nService" as SlaRuntime
participant "Live Event\nService" as Events

== 1. Submit message ==
Agent -> UI: Compose message, reply,\nor internal note
UI -> Routes: POST /api/tickets/:id/messages
Routes -> Guards: auth, active user/member,\nowner/admin/agent role
Routes -> Routes: validate type, body,\nattachmentFileIds
Routes -> Controller: createTicketMessageController(req)
Controller -> MessageService: createTicketMessage(workspaceId,\nticketId, userId, payload)

== 2. Validate ticket and attachments ==
MessageService -> TicketModels: load ticket and conversation\nfor workspace
MessageService -> MessageService: enforce closed-ticket rule
MessageService -> FileServices: if attachment ids supplied,\nload ready same-workspace files\nand check not already linked

== 3. Apply message and status side effects ==
alt public_reply
  MessageService -> MessageModel: create public reply message
  MessageService -> SlaRuntime: set firstResponseAt and\npause resolution SLA
  MessageService -> TicketModels: status = waiting_on_customer
else customer_message
  MessageService -> MessageModel: create customer message
  MessageService -> SlaRuntime: resume active resolution SLA\nwhen previously paused
  MessageService -> TicketModels: status = open
else internal_note
  MessageService -> MessageModel: create internal note
  MessageService -> TicketModels: keep current ticket status
end

== 4. Link attachments ==
MessageService -> FileServices: create message attachment links
MessageService -> FileServices: create ticket reverse links

== 5. Publish message event ==
MessageService -> TicketModels: update ticket/conversation\nmessage counters and summaries
MessageService -> Events: publish message.created\nand conversation.updated
MessageService --> Controller: message, conversation,\nticketSummary
Controller --> UI: success.ticket.messageCreated
UI --> Agent: Show updated thread

@enduml
